The paper proposes a data-driven approach to model pedestrian behavior using vehicle-mounted cameras, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of LSTM models and empirical analysis also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
